parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DPS system can cause the vehicle to become unstable and difficult to control, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: the steering becomes difficult to control
the vehicle goes into limp mode

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corruption of the Engine Control Module (ECM) can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing a loss of control or accident.
symptoms: The check engine light turns on
the temperature bar graph reaches 5 bars
and the engine runs on one cylinder.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spark Plug Wire Grounding and Engine Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The grounding of the spark plug wire can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: the spark plug wire is grounded to the head
the vehicle goes into limp mode
and the engine light turns on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) Fault and Engine Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The VSS fault can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: The VSS fault light turns on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control housing-switch can cause sudden and unexpected loss of vehicle speed, which can lead to accidents or put the driver and following vehicles at risk.
symptoms: making it difficult to control the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate at a high rate of speed, making it difficult or impossible to control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
and potentially causing accidents or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Pressure Buildup and Gasoline Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive pressure buildup in the fuel tank can cause gasoline to spew out, potentially leading to fires, explosions, or injuries from skin contact and inhalation of gasoline vapors.
symptoms: Hissing sound coming from the gas tank
gasoline and/or gas vapors spewing out of the gas tank when the gas cap is removed
skin contact and inhalation of gasoline vapors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning headlights can cause confusion on the road, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may mistakenly think the vehicle is an emergency vehicle.
symptoms: headlights flash continuously on low beam
headlights appear like those of an emergency vehicle.
